Prominent City attorney Noorudien Hassan was murdered when gunmen opened fire on him in Lansdowne on Monday night.Police spokesperson Noloyiso Rwexana said the incident happened at about 10pm in Burwood Road.No one has been arrested yet.Hassan has handled a number of high profile cases including representing Irshaad Laher, linked to the sale of thousands of firearms stolen by corrupt police colonel Christiaan Prinsloo, who admitted in court he had sold the weapons to gangs in Cape Town.&quot;The motive for the murder is yet to be established. Any person with information regarding the incident is kindly requested to contact Lansdowne Detectives on 021 700 9000 or 082 576 2804 or Crime Stop on 08600 10111,&quot; Rwexana said.